HEADWORD: Rancid
<hw>Ran"cid</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rancidus</ets>, fr. <ets>rancere</ets> to be rancid or rank.]</ety>
<def>Having a rank smell or taste, from chemical change or
decomposition; musty; <as>as, <ex>rancid</ex> oil or
butter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rancidity</ent>⟦br⟧
